{"TopicId":204522,"ForumId":106,"TopicTitle":"Scaling robotics parts","CreatedByName":"flart","CreatedById":181486,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-26T22:31:11Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"flart","CreatedById":181486,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-26T22:31:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyone was able to write a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Module Manager (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Module Manager (mod)\u0022\u003EMM\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E patch for a proper scaling\u00A0of the robotic parts?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nmy attempt have a strange bug that when you revert back from a flight, parts connected to a servo is scaled as the servo\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\u002BPART[rotoServo_04]\n{\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0@name = rotoServo-50\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0@title = Rotation Servo M-50 \u00A0// Rotation Servo M-25\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0%rescaleFactor = 2\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0@NODE,*\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0{\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0@size=2\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0}\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0@node_stack_bottom[6] = 4\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0@node_stack_top[6] = 4\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0@node_attach[6] = 4\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0@entryCost *= 2\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0@cost *= 2\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0@mass *= 8\n\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0@MODULE[ModuleRoboticRotationServo]\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0{\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0@maxMotorOutput *= 8\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0}\n}\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022fSkYVXf.jpeg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002250.90\u0022 height=\u0022538\u0022 width=\u00221057\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/fSkYVXf.jpeg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-06-30T22:06:41Z\u0022 title=\u002206/30/2022 10:06  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EJune 30, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by flart\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"flart","CreatedById":181486,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-27T14:09:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/187168-lisias/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022187168\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/187168-lisias/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Lisias\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Do you encounter this on your tweakscale research?\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-08-27T14:31:22Z\u0022 title=\u002208/27/2021 02:31  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 27, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by flart\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lisias","CreatedById":187168,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-27T14:37:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224024911\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204522\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221630073369\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022181486\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022flart\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/27/2021 at 11:09 AM, flart said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/187168-lisias/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022187168\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/187168-lisias/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Lisias\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Do you encounter this on your tweakscale research?\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYep, and some others problems as attaching nodes (I think some data may be linked directly into the prefab, and so mangling it mangle everybody else).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThese pesky problems are the reason I postponed support for Serenity for so many time, things are probably going to blow on my first attempts, and I need a stable environment to try these stunts - or I will never know when I had screwed up or its something else on KSP.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-09-05T07:15:59Z\u0022 title=\u002209/05/2021 07:15  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 5, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Lisias\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003ETyops! As usulla...\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"flart","CreatedById":181486,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-06-30T21:59:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nkspcommunityfixes 1.18 changelog mentions that the problem is fixed\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022163039\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1919060119\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/204002-18-112-kspcommunityfixes-bugfixes-and-qol-tweaks/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=4150113\u0026amp;embedComment=4150113\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022 style=\u0022height:297px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lisias","CreatedById":187168,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-01T05:28:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224150289\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204522\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221656626346\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022181486\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022flart\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, flart said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nkspcommunityfixes 1.18 changelog mentions that the problem is fixed\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you want to give it a try?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDownload and instal the \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/net-lisias-ksp/TweakScale/releases/tag/PRERELEASE%2F2.5.0.46\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Elatest TweakScale Beta 2.5\u003C/a\u003E , then create a folder on GameData called \u0022TweakScaleExperimental\u0022. This will trigger the Robotics patching.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rutabaga22","CreatedById":221143,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-12T18:02:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224150409\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204522\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221656653321\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022187168\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Lisias\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/1/2022 at 1:28 AM, Lisias said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you want to give it a try?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDownload and instal the \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/net-lisias-ksp/TweakScale/releases/tag/PRERELEASE%2F2.5.0.46\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Elatest TweakScale Beta 2.5\u003C/a\u003E , then create a folder on GameData called \u0022TweakScaleExperimental\u0022. This will trigger the Robotics patching.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI tried this and it isn\u0027t working. Do you know what isn\u0027t working?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lisias","CreatedById":187168,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-12T18:48:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224154188\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204522\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221657648934\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022221143\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Rutabaga22\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, Rutabaga22 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI tried this and it isn\u0027t working. Do you know what isn\u0027t working?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou are right. I forgot to include the Robotics into the Experimental program! Totally Alzheimer\u0027s fault, I will issue a new BETA today night with the robotics included on the Experimental program!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(I have the memories of working on it, but I probably lost the patches somewhere - probably ended up overwriting it on some test session and plain forgot about\u2026)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nazalassa","CreatedById":217956,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-12T21:57:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224024720\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204522\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221630017071\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022181486\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022flart\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/27/2021 at 12:31 AM, flart said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nparts connected to a servo is scaled as the servo\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI got the problem too, they scaled when the servo moved, in the VAP/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E and in flight.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lisias","CreatedById":187168,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-15T12:45:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGuys, since I had messed up my statements above (gee, I\u0027m getting old), I\u0027m working on the Experimental patches for the Robotics on the Beta branch of TweakScale.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut I need to confess, it doesn\u0027t look promising.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m pretty sure I will need to write something on Recall in order to coerce the damned Serenity PartModules into behave.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the mean time, I will really appreciate any report about the Serenity mishaps you get. Please report them here, or on this issue \u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/net-lisias-ksp/KSP-Recall/issues/53\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/net-lisias-ksp/KSP-Recall/issues/53\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u2014 \u2014\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGuys, I released TS Beta 2.5.0.49, with the Deployable Science and Robotics scaling on the \u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Courier New\u0027, Courier, monospace;\u0022\u003ETweakScaleExperimental\u003C/span\u003E status. See the post for more instructions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPartModule glitches are still there (the known and the unknown), we need to hunt them all so I can cook something on KSP-Recall.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022187168\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed7151306475\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/179030-ksp-130-tweakscale-under-lisias-management-24616-2022-0713/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=4155295\u0026amp;embedComment=4155295\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022 style=\u0022height:261px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKeep in mind that anything on Experimental can change at any moment - or even vanish. Don\u0027t start any long term gaming with them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPing \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/181486-flart/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022181486\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/181486-flart/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@flart\u003C/a\u003E, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/221143-rutabaga22/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022221143\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/221143-rutabaga22/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Rutabaga22\u003C/a\u003E, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/217956-nazalassa/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022217956\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/217956-nazalassa/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Nazalassa\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-07-16T09:38:55Z\u0022 title=\u002207/16/2022 09:38  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 16, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by Lisias\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003ETS beta 2.5.0.49\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}